President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. These include Elizabeth Sherwood-Randall as Deputy Secretary of the Department of Energy, Jess L. Baily as Ambassador to the Republic of Macedonia, Judith Beth Cefkin as Ambassador to the Republic of the Fiji Islands, the Republic of Kiribati, the Republic of Nauru, the Kingdom of Tonga, and Tuvalu, Robert Francis Cekuta as Ambassador to the Republic of Azerbaijan, S. Fitzgerald Haney as Ambassador to the Republic of Costa Rica, Ambassador Michele Jeanne Sison as Deputy Representative of the United States to the United Nations, and Margaret Ann Uyehara as Ambassador to Montenegro. President Obama expressed confidence in these individuals' abilities and looks forward to working with them.